
model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=30, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=50, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

1661/1 [] - 0s 34us/sample - loss: 0.5857 - accuracy: 0.6105
test_loss_zeros: 0.6547684294360501 - test_accuracy_zeros: 0.7101081
test_loss_ones: 0.5773976192927949 - test_accuracy_ones: 0.6104756

**************************************************
**************************************************

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.005, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=50, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.01, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=50, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.05, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=50, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.01, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=50, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.01, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=60, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.03, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=60, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(
    lr=0.03, beta_1=0.9, beta_2=0.999, epsilon=None,
    decay=0.0, amsgrad=False, clipnorm=1., clipvalue=0.5),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=200, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=200, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])

model = keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Input(21),
        keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dropout(0.1),
        keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(16, activation='relu'),
        keras.layers.Dense(2, activation='softmax')  # tanh, sigmoid, hard_sigmoid, softsign, relu
    ])
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='binary_crossentropy',  # sparse_categorical_crossentropy, binary_crossentropy, mean_squared_error
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(xy_train[:, :21], xy_train[:, 21:], epochs=60, verbose=2)
test_loss_zeros, test_acc_zeros = model.evaluate(xy_test_zeros[:, :21], xy_test_zeros[:, 21:])
test_loss_ones, test_acc_ones = model.evaluate(xy_test_ones[:, :21], xy_test_ones[:, 21:])
